The paper presents a graph processing system, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC) and database systems (cs.DB). The system also involves data structures and algorithms for efficient graph processing, which can be categorized under data structures (cs.DS) and performance (cs.PF). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of parallelism and scheduling, which can be classified under social and information networks (cs.SI).
